  "benefit_assessment_plain_language": "M4v still does not prove end-to-end Flye GPU speedup: CPU toy-raw elapsed 82s and the persistent lifecycle run elapsed 88s. The direct benefit is at the worker lifecycle seam: the actual warm request ran as request ordinal 2 with CUDA context warm, and its request_total was 8.223469 ms versus M4u batch-run worker_process_ms 440.793131 ms, a 98.134393% reduction in the measured per-request lifecycle cost. This shows the persistent worker seam can remove the dominant external startup/CUDA context cost, but the current proof still pays for a warmup request inside one Flye run and is not yet a whole-stage speedup.",
